results.name: Primes that are not squares mod 163.
comment: Inert rational primes in Q(sqrt -163). (Note that 41 is not inert in this field, it decomposes - see A296921.)
reference: Helmut Hasse, Number Theory, Grundlehren 229, Springer, 1980, page 498.
link: Index to sequences related to decomposition of primes in quadratic fields
maple: Load the Maple program HH given in A296920. Then run HH(-163,200); - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Dec 26 2017
program: (PARI) lista(nn) = forprime(p=2, nn, if (!issquare(Mod(p, 163)), print1(p, ", "));); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Dec 24 2017
results.author: _Ed Pegg Jr_, Dec 22 2017
